{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8741d675-5afc-4565-8f5d-7d9c7feadd79","content":"Here's the MTP equivalent:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nKey changes after the `--` separator (MTP args):\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays before `--` since `dotnet test` handles it.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n> **Note:** Native MTP support in `dotnet test` requires the **.NET 9+ SDK** (it can still target `net8.0`). If you're on the .NET 8 SDK, you'll need to run the compiled test binary directly instead of using `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b4c72c9d-8a00-4341-bf62-60fc66c499b1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` ã `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` ã `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` ã `--collect-coverage` with format option\n- `--blame-crash` ã `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` ã `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` ã `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- With .NET 8, you typically run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run --project` to invoke MTP, since `dotnet test` native MTP support came in .NET 9 SDK.\n- When using `dotnet test` with MTP, you pass arguments after the `--` separator.\n- The command-line options differ between the traditional test runner and MTP: filters work the same way, but logging requires the TrxReport extension package, code coverage needs the CodeCoverage package with different flag syntax, and crash/hang diagnostics use `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` respectively with their own extension packages.\n\nNow I'm realizing there's a version constraint hereãMTP support in `dotnet test` only arrived with .NET 9 SDK, so on .NET 8 the better approach is running the test executable directly rather than going through `dotnet test`.","outputTokens":1217,"requestId":"0BD6:33AAFA:233762:28FEA1:69F0053E"},"id":"b0897c92-fac7-48a8-b41f-cc52d930174a","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:54:43.822Z","parentId":"2e9c9c42-8b34-46ca-8bbf-9c6dbcf4ce64"}
